The following code fragment causes a segmentation fault if the `_speedups.c` version of `escape()` is used:
```py
from markupsafe import escape

class Test(object):
    def __html__(self):
        raise ValueError(123)

escape(Test())
```

I think the likely cause is that `PyObject_CallObject(html, NULL)` returns `NULL` on an exception, but the returned value is not checked for `NULL` before it is passed to `PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs()` and `Py_DECREF()`:

```c
	/* if the object has an __html__ method that performs the escaping */
	html = PyObject_GetAttr(text ,id_html);
	if (html) {
		s = PyObject_CallObject(html, NULL);
		Py_DECREF(html);
		/* Convert to Markup object */
		rv = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(markup, (PyObject*)s, NULL);
		Py_DECREF(s);
		return rv;
	}
```
